Cummins CEO Says He Needs to Hire 7,000 Engineers in 5 Years

-- B y   A d r i e l   B e t t e l h e i m
-- 
2011-10-05T14:05:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-05/cummins-ceo-says-he-needs-to-hire-7-000-engineers-in-5-years.html
Cummins Inc. (CMI)  needs to add 7,000
engineers within five years, Chairman and Chief Executive
Officer Theodore Solso said today at a Bloomberg Innovation and
Jobs Forum in  Washington .   The Columbus, Indiana-based maker of diesel and natural gas
engines also manufactures electric power generation systems.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Adriel Bettelheim in Washington at 
